<http://identifiers.org/rgd/1307121>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2457  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: LRRC4b expressed in non-neural cells induces functional presynaptic differentiation in contacting axons.\nDirect aggregation of LRRC4b on the surface of dendrites induces coclustering of excitatory postsynaptic proteins.\nLRRC4b interacts with LAR.\nSoluble LAR reduces LRRC4b-induced presynaptic differentiation.\n\n19/2/2018 Pim\n- Fig.6 features a cell-cell-aggregation assay that demonstrates the adhesive properties of LRRC4b.. Experimental description: Methods\nMixed-culture assay.\nBriefly, primary hippocampal neuron cultures at 10 d in vitro (10 DIV) prepared from embryonic day 18-19 (E18-19) rats were cocultured with HEK293T cells.\n\nDNA constructs and antibodies.\nFull-length human NGL-1 (NM_020929, amino acids 1-641) and rat NGL-3 (XM_218615, amino acids 1-709) were subcloned into pEGFP-N1 (Clontech). Human LAR (amino acids 1-1881) was subcloned into pECFP-N1 (Clontech)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2457" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

